I was planning to do that anyway as a cool kinda symbolism of growing up but I think the only thing that can replace this special boy is someone just as special.

summary:
Introducing a new character, Katrina!


She’s not a gym leader, just the regional flying type specialist of Qamor and she makes...
caption:
Introducing a new character, Katrina! She’s not a gym leader, just the regional flying type specialist of Qamor and she makes frequent appearances throughout the story. (Also, her ace is actually an Albacross but i couldn’t fit it in her artwork……..she does befriend a Numby during the story so it works lol)

“Hey, you Slowpokes need a lift to the next town over? I got some packages that need delivered over there and, I mean, it sure beats walking. So I suggest taking head of my generosity!”

Working for her parent’s mail carrier service, Katrina fly’s throughout Qamor on her trusty sea-plane The Scarlet Pelipper delivering parcels and mail that need to be delivered around the region. Katrina’s services are always dependable and on time, she’s devices a perfect system of flying around the region counter-clockwise along with Qamor’s natural air currents dropping off and picking up mail orders. She always fly’s with her trusty partner Albacross who comes in handy during thunderstorms, who redirects lightning that might strike her plane. Since she’s constantly traveling around the region, on the side Katrina reports and studies meteorological conditions in Qamor. Numby and Munsun she meets while flying around often help her make these reports and in return she feeds them treats.

Katrina is a pretty popular person in Qamor, everyone appreciates her services and high spirited personality- even if she’s often smart mouthed and quick witted. She often likes teasing and messing with the Main Character Crew but offers them help and guidance when they need it.

summary: With Spearow and Fearow, I altered the main feathers to a more bronze color. I prefered the original beak and feet color, so I...
caption: With Spearow and Fearow, I altered the main feathers to a more bronze color. I prefered the original beak and feet color, so I reverted them back to normal. With the wings I thought they looked nice as a pale purple, while the head feathers on Fearow looked better darker.
